<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

    <PropertyGroup>
        <Authors>Alastair Lundy</Authors>
        <Company />
        <Description>Cross-platform Operating System Detection, Operating System Version Detection, Apple Silicon Mac Detection, programmatic .NET Runtime ID Generation, and more. For a full list of features please visit: https://github.com/alastairlundy/PlatformKit/blob/main/docs/FeatureComparisonByPlatform.md</Description>
        <Copyright>Copyright (c) Alastair Lundy 2018-2024</Copyright>
        <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/alastairlundy/PlatformKit/</RepositoryUrl>
        <PackageRequireLicenseAcceptance>true</PackageRequireLicenseAcceptance>
        <RepositoryType>git</RepositoryType>
        <PackOnBuild>true</PackOnBuild>
        <PackageId>PlatformKit</PackageId>
        <Owners>AlastairLundy</Owners>
        <Summary>PlatformKit is a library dealing with Platform specific code, platform specific issues, and platform detection in C# .NET Core.</Summary>
        <PackageTags>platform detection, CSharp,</PackageTags>
        <Title>PlatformKit</Title>
        <PackageReleaseNotes>### Changes since 4.0.0 Beta 1
* Renamed ``ProcessManager`` class to ``ProcessRunner`` and moved Command functionality to ``CommandRunner``.
* Renamed methods in ``ProcessRunner`` and ``CommandRunner`` better reflect what they do.
* Added the ``AppModel`` class to represent Apps installed on a device.
* Added the ``InstalledApps`` class to assist with detecting and opening InstalledApps - For now detecting installed apps is implemented on Linux and FreeBsd. Windows and macOS implementations will be added in a future version.
* Changed the ``SteamOsAnalyzer`` class to extend the LinuxAnalyzer class.
* Made some extension methods for Strings and Versions internal only as they didn't need to be public.
* Added the ``Platform`` enum to represent different Platforms (e.g. Windows, Mac, Linux etc).
* Renamed ``OsAnalyzer`` to ``PlatformAnalyzer``.
* Renamed methods in ``WindowsAnalyzer``, ``LinuxAnalyzer``, ``MacOsAnalyzer``, and ``FreeBsdAnalyzer`` to start with ``Get`` instead of ``Detect`` for detection based methods.
* Marked ConsoleHelper class for deprecation and removal in PlatformKit 5
* Fixed an issue where ``FreeBsdAnalyzer`` would check if it was being run on Windows instead of FreeBSD.</PackageReleaseNotes>
   <Product>PlatformKit</Product>
        <LangVersion>default</LangVersion>
        <AutoGenerateBindingRedirects>true</AutoGenerateBindingRedirects>
        <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>
        <PackageLicenseFile>LICENSE.txt</PackageLicenseFile>
        <TargetFrameworks>net6.0;netstandard2.0;net8.0</TargetFrameworks>
   <AssemblyVersion>4.0.0.0</AssemblyVersion>
        <FileVersion>4.0.0.0</FileVersion>
        <Version>4.0.0-beta.2</Version>
        <PackageVersion>4.0.0-beta.2</PackageVersion>
        <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/alastairlundy/PlatformKit/</PackageProjectUrl>
        <GeneratePackageOnBuild>true</GeneratePackageOnBuild>
        <PackageIcon>platformkit_logo_512x.jpg</PackageIcon>
        <IncludeContentInPack>true</IncludeContentInPack>
    </PropertyGroup>

    <ItemGroup>
        <None Include="..\images\logos\platformkit_logo_512x.jpg">
          <Pack>True</Pack>
          <PackagePath></PackagePath>
          <Link>platformkit_logo_512x.jpg</Link>
        </None>
        
        <None Include="../README.md" Pack="true" PackagePath="\" />
    </ItemGroup>

    <ItemGroup>
      <Folder Include="Platforms" />
    </ItemGroup>

    <ItemGroup>
      <Content Include="..\LICENSE.txt">
        <Link>LICENSE.txt</Link>
          <PackagePath>LICENSE.txt</PackagePath>
          <CopyToOutputDirectory>Always</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      </Content>
    </ItemGroup>
</Project>